\qj \fi144\li0\ri0\sl300\slmult1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid14484228 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs15\f37\fs36\cf15\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 Having risen from sleep, we fall down before Thee, O Good One, and the angelic hymn we cry aloud to Thee, O Mighty One. Holy, Holy, Holy art Thou. O God; through the Theotokos, have mercy on us.
\par 
\par Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit. 
\par 
\par From bed and sleep hast Thou raised me up, O Lord: enlighten my mind and heart and open my lips that I may hymn Thee, O Holy Trinity: 
\par 
\par Holy, Holy, Holy art Thou, O God; through the Theotokos, have mercy on us. 
\par 
\par Both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par Suddenly the judge shall come, and the deeds of each shall be laid bare; but with fear do we cry at midnight. Holy, Holy, Holy art Thou, O God; through the Theotokos, have mercy on us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid14484228 \sect }\sectd \ltrsect\psz1\sbknone\linex0\endnhere\titlepg\sectlinegrid360\sectdefaultcl\sectrsid14484228\sftnbj \pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \fi144\li0\ri0\sl300\slmult1
