\par Lord, have mercy. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f47\fs20\cf6\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 Twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f47\fs20\cf6\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 Prayer of Saint Basil the Great to the Most Holy Trinity:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid15815530 \sect }\sectd \ltrsect\psz1\sbknone\linex0\cols2\colsx288\linebetcol\endnhere\titlepg\sectlinegrid360\sectdefaultcl\sectrsid15815530\sftnbj \pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \fi144\li0\ri0\sl300\slmult1
\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid14484228 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 
As I rise from sleep, I thank Thee, O Holy Trinity, for through Thy great goodness
 and patience Thou wast not angry with me, an idler and sinner, nor hast Thou destroyed me with mine iniquities, but hast shown Thy usual love for mankind; and when I was prostrate in despair, Thou hast raised me up to keep the morning watch and glorify T
hy power. And now enlighten my mind's eye, and open my mouth that I may meditate on Thy words, and understand Thy commandments, and do Thy will, and hymn Thee in heartfelt confession, and sing praises to Thine all-holy name: of the Father, and of the Son,
 and of the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid15815530 \sect }\sectd \ltrsect\psz1\sbknone\linex0\endnhere\titlepg\sectlinegrid360\sectdefaultcl\sectrsid14484228\sftnbj \pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \fi144\li0\ri0\sl300\slmult1
\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid14484228 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 

\par O come let us worship God our King.
\par O come let us worship and fall down before Christ our King and God.
\par O come let us worship and fall down before Christ Himself, our King and God.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f47\fs20\cf6\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 PSALM 50}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid15815530 \sect }\sectd \ltrsect\psz1\sbknone\linex0\cols2\colsx288\linebetcol\endnhere\titlepg\sectlinegrid360\sectdefaultcl\sectrsid15815530\sftnbj \pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \fi144\li0\ri0\sl300\slmult1
\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid14484228 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 
Have mercy on me, O God, according to Thy great mercy; and according to the multitude of Thy compassions blot out my transgression. Wash me thoroughly from mine iniquity, and cleanse me from my sin.
\par 
\par For I know mine iniquity, and my sin is ever before me. Against Thee only have I sinned and done this evil before Thee, that Thou mightest be justified in Thy words, and prevail when Thou art judged. 
\par 
\par For behold, I was conceived in iniquities, and in sins did my mother bear me. For behold, Thou hast loved truth; the hidden and secret things of Thy wisdom hast Thou made manifest unto me. 
\par 
\par Thou shalt sprinkle me with hyssop, and I shall be made clean; Thou shalt wash me, and I shall be made whiter than snow. 
\par 
\par Thou shalt make me to hear joy and gladness; the bones that be humbled, they shall rejoice. 
\par 
\par Turn Thy face away from my sins, and blot out all mine iniquities. 
\par 
\par Create in me a clean heart, O God, and renew a right spirit within me. 
\par 
\par Cast me not away from Thy presence, and take not Thy Holy Spirit from me. 
\par 
\par Restore unto me the joy of Thy salvation, and with Thy governing Spirit establish me. 
\par 
\par I shall teach transgressors Thy ways, and the ungodly shall turn back unto Thee. 
\par 
\par Deliver me from bloodguiltiness. O God, Thou God of my salvation; my tongue shall rejoice in Thy righteousness. 
\par 
\par O Lord, Thou shalt open my lips, and my mouth shall declare Thy praise. 
\par 
\par For if Thou hadst desired sacrifice, I had given it; with wholeburnt offerings Thou shalt not be pleased. 
\par 
\par A sacrifice unto God is a broken spirit; a heart that is broken and humbled God will not despise. 
\par 
\par Do good, O Lord, in Thy good pleasure unto Sion, and let the walls of Jerusalem be builded. 
\par 
\par Then shalt Thou be pleased with a sacrifice of righteousness, with oblation and wholeburnt offerings. 
\par 
\par Then shall they offer bullocks upon Thine altar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid15815530 \sect }\sectd \ltrsect\psz1\sbknone\linex0\endnhere\titlepg\sectlinegrid360\sectdefaultcl\sectrsid14484228\sftnbj \pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \fi144\li0\ri0\sl300\slmult1
