\ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f47\fs20\cf6\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 The Symbol of the Orthodox Faith:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid15815530 \sect }\sectd \ltrsect\psz1\sbknone\linex0\headery0\cols2\colsx288\linebetcol\endnhere\titlepg\sectlinegrid360\sectdefaultcl\sectrsid15815530\sftnbj \pard\plain \ltrpar
\qj \fi144\li0\ri0\sl300\slmult1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid14484228 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f37\fs32\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 I believe in one God, the Father Almighty, Maker of heaven and earth, and of all things visible and invisible. 
\par 
\par And in one Lord Jesus Christ. the Son of God, the Only-begotten, begotten of the Father before all ages. Light of Light; true God of true God, begotten, not made; of one essence with the Father by Whom all things were made; Who for us men, and for our sal
vation, came down from the heavens,  and was incarnate of the Holy Spirit and the Virgin Mary, and became man; And was crucified for us under Po
ntius Pilate, and suffered, and was buried; And arose again on the third day according to the Scriptures; And ascended into the heavens, and sitteth at the right hand of the Father. And shall come again, with glory, to judge both the living and the dead; 
Whose kingdom shall have no end. 
\par 
\par And in the Holy Spirit, the Lord, the Giver of Life; Who proceedeth from the Father; Who with the Father and the Son together is worshipped and glorified; Who spake by the prophets. 
\par 
\par In One, Holy, Catholic, and Apostolic Church. I confess one baptism for the remission of sins. I look for the resurrection of the dead, And the life of the age to come. Amen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid15815530 \sect }\sectd \ltrsect\psz1\sbknone\linex0\headery0\endnhere\titlepg\sectlinegrid360\sectdefaultcl\sectrsid15815530\sftnbj \pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \fi144\li0\ri0\sl300\slmult1
\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid14484228 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f47\fs20\cf6\insrsid15815530 \sect }\sectd \ltrsect\psz1\sbknone\linex0\headery0\cols2\colsx288\linebetcol\endnhere\titlepg\sectlinegrid360\sectdefaultcl\sectrsid15815530\sftnbj \pard\plain \ltrpar
\qj \fi144\li0\ri0\sl300\slmult1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid14484228 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs29\i\f47\fs20\cf6\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 Prayer I, of St. Macarius the Great:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 
\par 
\par O God, cleanse me a sinner, for I have never done anything good in Thy sight; but deliver me from the evil one, and let Thy will be done in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid11541725\charrsid14484228 in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228  me, that I may open mine unworthy mouth without condemnation, and praise Thy holy name: of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f47\fs20\cf6\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 Prayer II, of the same saint:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 
\par 
\par Having risen from sleep, I offer unto Thee, O Saviour, the midnight hymn, and falling down I cry unto Thee: Grant me not to fall asleep in the death of sin, but have compassion on me, O Thou Who wast voluntarily crucified, and hasten to raise me who am re
clining in idleness, and save me in prayer and intercession; and after the night's sleep shine upon me a sinless day, O Christ God, and save me.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f47\fs20\cf6\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 Prayer III, of the same saint:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 
\par 
\par Having risen from sleep, I hasten to Thee, O Master, Lover of mankind, and by Thy loving-kindness, I strive to do Thy work, and I pray to Thee: Help me at all times, in everything, and deliver me from every worldly, evil thing and every impulse of the dev
il, and save me, and lead me into Thine eternal kingdom. For Thou art my Creator, and the Giver, and Provider of everything good, and in Thee is all my hope, and unto Thee do I send up glory, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f47\fs20\cf6\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 Prayer IV, of the same saint:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 
\par 
\par O Lord, Who in Thine abundant goodness and Thy great compassion hast granted me, Thy servant, to go through the time of the night that is past without attack from any opposing evil: Do Thou Thyself, O Master, Creator of all things, vouchsafe me by Thy tru
e light and with an enlightened heart to do Thy will, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f47\fs20\cf6\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 Prayer V, of St. Basil the Great:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 
\par 
\par O Lord Almighty, God of hosts and of all flesh, Who dwellest on high and lookest down on things that are lowly, Who searchest the heart and innermost being, and clearly foreknowest the secrets of men; O unoriginate and everlasting Light, with Whom is no v
ariableness, neither shadow of turning: 
\par 
\par Do Thou, O Immortal King, receive our supplications which we, daring because of the multitude of Thy compassions, offer Thee at the present time from defiled lips; and forgive u
s our sins, in deed, word, and thought, whether committed by us knowingly or in ignorance, and cleanse us from every defilement of flesh and spirit. 
\par 
\par And grant us to pass through the night of the whole present life with watchful heart and sober thought, ever expecting the coming of the bright and appointed day of Thine Only-begotten Son, our Lord and God and Saviour, Jesus Christ, whereon the judge of 
all shall come with glory to reward each according to his deeds. 
\par 
\par May we not be found fallen and idle, bu
t watching, and upright in activity, ready to accompany Him into the joy and divine palace of His glory, where there is the ceaseless sound of those that keep festival, and the unspeakable delight of those that behold the ineffable beauty of Thy countenan
ce. 
\par 
\par For Thou art the true Light that enlightenest and sanctifiest all, and all creation doth hymn Thee unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f47\fs20\cf6\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 Prayer VI, likewise by St. Basil:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 
\par 
\par We bless Thee, O Most High God and Lord of mercy, Who ever doest with us things both great and inscrutable, both glorious and awesome, of which there is no measure; Who grantest to us sleep for rest from our infirmities, and relaxation from the labors of 
our much toiling flesh. 
\par 
\par We thank Thee that Thou hast not destroyed us with our iniquities, but hast shown Thy loving-kindness to man as usual, and while we were lying in despair upon our beds, Thou hast raised us up that we might glorify Thy dominion. 
\par 
\par Wherefore, we implore Thy boundless goodness: Enlighten the eyes of our understanding and raise up our mind from the heavy sleep of indolence; open our mouth and fill it with Thy praise, that we may be able steadily to hymn and confess Thee, Who art God g
lorified in all and by all, the unoriginate Father, with Thine Only-begotten Son, and Thine All-holy and good and life-creating Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f47\fs20\cf6\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 {\*\bkmkstart _Hlk181010412}Prayer }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f47\fs20\cf6\insrsid8936126 7, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs29\i\f47\fs20\cf6\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 to the Most Holy Theotokos:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 
\par 
\par I sing of thy grace, O Sovereign Lady, and I pray thee to grace my mind. 
\par 
\par Teach me to step aright in. the way of Christ's commandments. 
\par 
\par Strengthen me to keep awake in song, and drive away the sleep of despondency. 
\par 
\par O Bride of God, by thy prayers release me, bound with the bonds of sin.
\par 
\par Guard me by night and by day, and deliver me from foes that defeat me.
\par 
\par O bearer of God the Life-giver, enliven me who am deadened by passions.
\par 
\par O bearer of the unwaning Light, enlighten my blinded soul.
\par 
\par O marvelous palace of the Master, make me to be a house of the Divine Spirit.
\par 
\par O bearer of the Healer, heal the perennial passions of my soul.
\par 
\par Guide me to the path of repentance, for I am tossed in the storm of life.
\par 
\par Deliver me from eternal fire, and from evil worms, and from Tartarus.
\par 
\par Let me not be exposed to the rejoicing of demons, guilty as I am of many sins.
\par 
\par Renew me, grown old from senseless sins, O most immaculate one.
\par 
\par Present me untouched by all torments, and pray for me to the Master of all.
\par 
\par Vouchsafe me to find the joys of heaven with all the saints.
\par 
\par O most holy Virgin, hearken unto the voice of thine unprofitable servant.
\par 
\par Grant me torrents of tears, O most pure one, to cleanse my soul from impurity.
\par 
\par I offer the groans of my heart to thee unceasingly, strive for me, O Sovereign Lady.
\par 
\par Accept my service of supplication and offer it to compassionate God.
\par 
\par O thou who art above the angels, raise me above this world's confusion.
\par 
\par O Light bearing heavenly tabernacle, direct the grace of the Spirit in me.
\par 
\par I raise my hands and lips in thy praise, defiled as they are by impurity, O all immaculate one. 
\par 
\par Deliver me from soul corrupting evils, and fervently intercede with Christ, to Whom is due honor and worship, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f47\fs20\cf6\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 Prayer }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f47\fs20\cf6\insrsid8936126 8, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs29\i\f47\fs20\cf6\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 to our Lord Jesus Christ:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 
\par 
\par O my plenteously merciful and all merciful God, Lord Jesus Christ, through Thy great love Thou didst come down and become incarnate so that Thou mightest save all. 
\par 
\par And again, O Saviour, save me by Thy grace, I pray Thee. For if Thou shouldst save me for my works, this would not be grace or a gift, but rather a duty; yea, Thou Who art great in compassion and ineffable in mercy. 
\par 
\par For he that believeth in Me, Thou hast said, O my Christ, shall live and never see death. If, then, faith in Thee saveth the desperate, behold, I believe, save me, for Thou art my God and Creator. 
\par 
\par Let faith instead of works be imputed to me, O my God, for Thou wilt find no works which could justify me. But may my faith suffice instead of all works, may it answer for, may it acquit me, may it make me a partaker of Thine eternal glory. 
\par 
\par And let Satan not seize me and boast, O Word, that he hath torn me from Thy hand and fold. But whether I desire it or not, save me, O Christ my Saviour, forestall me quickly, quickly, for I perish. 
\par 
\par Thou art my God from my mother's womb. Vouchsafe me, O Lord, to love Thee now as fervently as I once loved sin itself, and also to work for Thee without idleness, diligently, as I worked before for deceptive Satan. 
\par 
\par But supremely shall I work for Thee, my Lord and God, Jesus Christ, all the days of my life, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f47\fs20\cf6\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 {\*\bkmkend _Hlk181010412}Prayer IX, to the Holy Guardian Angel:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 
\par 
\par O holy angel that standeth by my wretched soul and my passionate life, forsake not me a sinner, nor shrink from me because of mine intemperance. 
\par Give no place for the cunning demon to master me through the violence of my mortal body, strengthen my poor and feeble hand, and guide me in the way of salvation. 
\par 
\par Yea, O holy angel of God, guardian and protector of my wretched soul and body, forgive me all wherein I have offended thee all the days of my life; and if I have sinned during the past night, protect me during the present day, and guard me from every temp
tation of the enemy, that I may not anger God by any sin. 
\par 
\par And pray to the Lord for me, that He may establish me in His fear, and show me, His servant, to be worthy of His goodness. Amen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f47\fs20\cf6\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 Prayer X, to the Most Holy Theotokos:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 
\par 
\par O my most holy lady Theotokos, through thy holy and all-powerful prayers, banish from me, thy lowly and wretched servant, despondency, forgetfulness, folly, carelessness, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs29\i\f47\fs20\cf6\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 (some will insert here specific sins and passions which afflict them)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 
 and all filthy, evil, and blasphemous thoughts from my wretched heart and my darkened mind. And quench the flame of my passions, for I am poor and wretched, and deliver me from many and cruel memories and deeds, and free me from all their evil effects. F
or blessed art thou by all generations, and glorified is thy most honourable name unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f47\fs20\cf6\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 Prayerful Invocation of the Saint Whose Name we bear:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 
\par 
\par Pray unto God for me, O holy God pleaser }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f47\fs20\cf6\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 N.,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 
 for I fervently flee unto Thee, the speedy helper and intercessor for my soul.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f47\fs20\cf6\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 Song to the Most Holy Theotokos:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 
\par 
\par O Theotokos and Virgin, rejoice, Mary, full of grace, the Lord is with thee; blessed art thou among women, and blessed is the Fruit of thy womb, for thou hast borne the Saviour of our souls.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f47\fs20\cf6\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 Troparion to the Cross:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\f37\fs36\cf15\insrsid8156083\charrsid14484228 
Save, O Lord, Thy people, and bless Thine inheritance; grant Thou victory to Orthodox Christians over enemies; and by the power of Thy Cross do Thou preserve Thy commonwealth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs32\insrsid15815530 \sect }\sectd \ltrsect\psz1\sbknone\linex0\headery0\endnhere\titlepg\sectlinegrid360\sectdefaultcl\sectrsid15815530\sftnbj \pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \fi144\li0\ri0\sl300\slmult1
